{\par \b Syntax:}\par STARTVIEW(ViewNumber[,Redraw])\par
{\par \b Description:}\par Starts a view of the current app. Redraw, is optional; if Redraw, is true (non 0), it will force a refresh for the view.\par \par The view numbers are as follows:\par 0=Symbolic\par 1=Plot\par 2=Numeric\par 3=Symbolic Setup\par 4=Plot Setup\par 5=Numeric Setup\par 6=App Info\par 7=Views key\par \par \par If the current app has views defined under the Views menu, then the following view numbers are used:\par 8=First special view (Split Screen Plot Detail)\par 9=Second special view (Split Screen Plot Table)\par 10=Third special view (Autoscale)\par 11=Fourth special view (Decimal)\par 12=Fifth special view (Integer)\par 13=Sixth special view (Trig)\par \par \par If ViewNumber is negative, the following global views are used:\par -1=HomeScreen\par -2=Modes\par -3=Memory Manager\par -4=App Library\par -5=Matrix Catalog\par -6=List Catalog\par -7=Program Catalog\par -8=Note Catalog\par
